%% Data Flow Diagram for vLLM Gaudi
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client / KServe Router
    participant Gateway as KServe Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OpenAI as OpenAI API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant TGIS as TGIS gRPC Adapter<br/>8033/TCP gRPC
    participant Engine as Async LLM Engine<br/>ZMQ IPC
    participant Worker as HPU Worker(s)<br/>Local / Ray
    participant HPU as Gaudi HPU Device<br/>PCIe

    Note over Client, HPU: Flow 1: OpenAI-Compatible Inference Request

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>OpenAI: Forward request<br/>HTTP(S)/8000, Bearer Token (optional)
    OpenAI->>OpenAI: Validate auth (if --api-key set)<br/>Parse request, create prompt
    OpenAI->>Engine: Submit request<br/>ZMQ IPC (local)
    Engine->>Engine: Schedule & batch<br/>Continuous batching
    Engine->>Worker: Execute inference<br/>PyTorch distributed
    Worker->>HPU: Forward pass<br/>PCIe/Device, PagedAttention
    HPU-->>Worker: Generated tokens
    Worker-->>Engine: Token output
    Engine-->>OpenAI: Streaming/complete response
    OpenAI-->>Gateway: JSON response<br/>(or SSE stream)
    Gateway-->>Client: HTTPS response

    Note over Client, HPU: Flow 2: TGIS gRPC Inference Request

    participant TGISClient as KServe / TGIS Client

    TGISClient->>TGIS: GenerationService.Generate<br/>gRPC/8033, plaintext
    TGIS->>OpenAI: Proxy to HTTP API<br/>HTTP/8000, localhost
    OpenAI->>Engine: Submit request<br/>ZMQ IPC
    Engine->>Worker: Execute inference
    Worker->>HPU: Forward pass
    HPU-->>Worker: Generated tokens
    Worker-->>Engine: Token output
    Engine-->>OpenAI: Response
    OpenAI-->>TGIS: HTTP response
    TGIS-->>TGISClient: gRPC response

    Note over Client, HPU: Flow 3: Prometheus Metrics Collection

    participant Prom as Prometheus

    Prom->>OpenAI: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP/8000, Optional TLS
    OpenAI-->>Prom: Prometheus metrics<br/>text/plain
